fields.name: Online shop
fields.description:
Product was developed using Django /Python/ and Javascript,
Its main characteristics are:

- products catalog

- shopping cart using Django sessions

- customer orders management

- sending asynchronous notifications to customers using Celery a distributed task queue (as a message broker I choosed RabbitMQ)

- payment gateway integration using Braintree

- custom views for administration site

- generating PDF invoices and sending them by email

- coupon system to apply discounts

- internalization

- translation using Rosetta

- product recommendation engine

fields.name: Levenshtein distance
fields.description:
In information theory, linguistics and computer science, the Levenshtein distance is a string metric for measuring the difference between two sequences.

Both are command line programs, one is creating a matrix column by column, the other row by row.

The patron sequence of nucleotides (35) is being comparing to sequences of up to 140.220 nucleotides.

fields.name: Earthquakes info
fields.description:
It´s a command line program built with python and using object-oriented progrmming concept.

Created mainly to work on "datos.csv" file which contains 25000 registers of earthquakes around the globe between 1970 and 2018.

There are 5 option to choose between the menu displayed on the screen:

1. Display the strongest earthquake between two dates.
2. Display an average magnitud ocurred in a given region between two dates.
3. Show a bar chart of earthquakes occured in a chosen part of the world during a given range of time.
4. Save in csv file the info about events that taken place between two selected dates.
5. Exit the program.

fields.name: Life expectancy /data cleaning/
fields.description:
The data were scrapped from Global Burden of Disease Study 2013 report which contains information about 263 countries between 1990 and 2013.

I used Request and BeautifulSoup Python library to pull data out of HTML.

Pandas library served to clean and tidy the data.

Finally the cleaned data were written in csv file.

I created an algorithm to check which countries experienced exponentially the life expectancy growth and printed the data on the screen.

fields.name: Abalone /data analysis/
fields.description:
Abalone (in Spanish abulón) is a common name for any of a group of small to very large marine molluscs.
The file contains 4177 instances, 8 attributes each.

I imported data in two ways: from a local csv file and a json file from web.

The data are tided and analysed using pandas library.
